benefits.description: All the benefits of Delta Comfort, plus...
Spacious seat with extra legroom and recline
Sky Priority® check-in and security access where available
Board first with Delta First boarding
Premium meals (on longer flights) with personalized flight attendant service

FIRST.upsellDescription: Find a relaxing reprieve in Delta First for more seamless travel with attentive service, greater personal space and priority access at the airport. Board first, settle in sooner and enjoy a quiet cabin up front with thoughtful touches designed to anticipate your every need.
FIRST.upsellConfirmation: All passengers on this confirmation number will be upgraded at a price-per-passenger rate, including taxes and fees. If you haven't selected seats, they will be auto-assigned. Your previously assigned seats will remain until then.
FIRST.refundabilityDisclaimer: Changeability and refundability are based on the fare rules of the original booked ticket (most tickets are nonrefundable). Terms Apply.
FIRST.seatLegendIconAlt: Magenta  indicates a First Class Seat
FIRST.brandTeaser: Find a relaxing reprieve from your travel day in Delta First, offering attentive service and greater personal space on your flight. Move quickly through your travel day with Sky Priority® check-in, security and baggage handling. You’re invited to board first so you can access dedicated bin space and settle in sooner. During your flight, enjoy a calming cabin with amenities that go the extra mile. Plus, find more space to relax or be productive, with ample armrest and tray space for a drink and your personal electronic devices.
FIRST.popOverContentBody: An elevated experience in Delta First
FIRST.parentShortBrandDescription: This flight is operated by a partner airline. Please visit the partner airline’s website for information about their seat and cabin experiences.

exitRowQualificationItems: You must be able to understand and speak English
You must be able to comprehend verbal instructions for operating the emergency exit, including visually locating and operating a window exit or exit door and directing others to the exit
You must be physically able to quickly activate the evacuation slide and help others off to it
You must be physically able to open an exit door and lift and stow a window exit weighing up to 60lb (28kgs)
You must not  have a condition that might cause you harm if called upon to perform an applicable exit row function
You must not require the use of a seat belt extension due to the hazard of entanglement
You cannot be under 15 years of age or traveling with a child under the age of 15
You cannot be traveling with an animal in the cabin of the aircraft
You cannot be traveling with supplemental oxygen or a wheelchair
contentMessages.exitRowQualificationTitle: Federal regulations require that passengers meet a set of criteria in order to be seated in an exit.
